  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Promote Healthy Life for Children (PHLC)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1) Increase access to play areas to establish a stress free living for children. 2)Increase access to nutritional meals and participation of mothers in providing the nutritional meals. 3) Increase interaction among children from two ethnicities (Tamil &amp;amp; Sinhala) in 3 resettled and border villages and to establish a long term peace through children as change agents in the communities.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Promote Healthy Life for Children aims to promote healthy and peaceful living for war affected children. The project expects to promote healthy and peaceful environment for children to overcome their grief and provide supplementary food for six months to support the nutrition of children until the families could afford and/or the dairy farmers societies formed by WC could support the children.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
